      <section eId="sec_CCP-4863">
        <num>CCP 4863</num>
        <heading>4863.  Determination of recusal; appointment of judge ad hoc</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4863__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In a parish or city court having more than one judge, the motion to recuse shall
be tried by another judge of the same court.  The manner in which the judge is selected to try
the recusal shall be provided by rule of court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4863__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In all other cases, the motion shall be tried by an ad hoc judge appointed by the
supreme court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112101</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
